COU5
The ancient tree looms over you and creaks slowly in the breeze. It stands out as the most life-like thing in the courtyard, even more than the birds. The spruce is an evergreen, genus Picea, with stiff sharp needles. The closely-spaced branches make climbing a possibility.
The closely-spaced branches of the spruce make the climb easier than in most trees, however the stiff spruce needles scrape and jab your skin through your flannel shirt.
Drilling a small hole into the trunk allows a small sample of sap to ooze out.
There doesn't seem to be much...